<Base title="Writing — Mike Hnath">

  <div class="section">
    <div class="page-title">Writing</div>
    <div class="page-subtitle">Brand strategy, marketing ops, and the occasional op-ed. More coming as THIS relaunches.</div>
    <div class="writing-row">
      <div class="writing-date">Coming soon</div>
      <div class="writing-body">
        <div class="writing-title">Why "brand strategy" is the most overused and least understood phrase in marketing</div>
        <div class="writing-excerpt">Everyone claims to do it. Most people mean "we made a logo and a deck." Here's what it actually means to build a brand system that does work in the market.</div>
        <div class="writing-tags"><span class="writing-tag">Brand</span><span class="writing-tag">Strategy</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="writing-arrow">→</div>
    </div>
    <div class="writing-row">
      <div class="writing-date">Coming soon</div>
      <div class="writing-body">
        <div class="writing-title">What managing $1M in pharma media taught me about regulated creative</div>
        <div class="writing-excerpt">MLR sign-off on every asset, 25 campaigns running simultaneously, and a DSP migration mid-flight. The discipline it builds is transferable to any regulated industry.</div>
        <div class="writing-tags"><span class="writing-tag">Performance</span><span class="writing-tag">Healthcare</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="writing-arrow">→</div>
    </div>
    <div class="writing-row">
      <div class="writing-date">Coming soon</div>
      <div class="writing-body">
        <div class="writing-title">The music industry taught me everything I needed to know about go-to-market</div>
        <div class="writing-excerpt">Booking 350 shows. Building audience from zero. Negotiating with labels. There's no better training ground for a growth marketer than indie music in 2009.</div>
        <div class="writing-tags"><span class="writing-tag">GTM</span><span class="writing-tag">Brand</span><span class="writing-tag">Personal</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="writing-arrow">→</div>
    </div>
    <div style="padding:20px 0;color:var(--text3);font-size:12px;text-align:center">More writing coming soon. Subscribe to stay updated.</div>
  </div>

</Base>
